      "content": "i get that there's no \"official\" report on it, but that's exactly the point. they wouldnt report it. if u look at the timing of the packets, they aren't randomized. they're timed to coincide with peak usage hours when everyone's brain activity is most active on their devices. it feels like they're using the update to bridge the gap between machine learning and human neural patterns. don't u think it's suspicious how much more data they've been pulling since the last major patch? like, why does a kernel update need this level of granular, constant biometric-adjacent telemetry?",
